"{\"uid\": \"csmonitor.com-World-Olympics-2024-0805-katie-ledecky-fourth-consecutive-gold-history-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our name is about honesty.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 26, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Monitor is owned by The First Church of Christ, Scientist, and we have always been transparent about that.\", \"from\": 27, \"to\": 137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The church publishes the Monitor because it sees good journalism as vital to progress in the world.\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since 1908, we have aimed \\\"to injure no man, but to bless all mankind,\\\" as our founder, Mary Baker Eddy, put it.\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 327, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Baker_Eddy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mary Baker Eddy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Baker_Eddy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Baker_Eddy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, you will find award-winning journalism not driven by commercial influences - a news organization that takes seriously its mission to uplift the world by seeking solutions and finding reasons for credible hope.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A deeper view that unites instead of divides, connecting why the story matters to you.\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A midsummer study by the International Council on Clean Transportation found that the average electric car produces 73% less greenhouse gas emissions over its lifespan than its gas-powered counterpart.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That sounds good, but it obscures a cost.\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ores that power our EVs and iPhones are fuel cells for conflict, corruption, and human exploitation in central Africa.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 934, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPhone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"iPhones\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPhone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPhone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet what if key players in the region were able to dig deep into veins of unity and agency?\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need to bring everyone to the table, not just the Rwandans and Congolese, but also the Burundians, Ugandans, Tanzanians, and all the stakeholders who profit from the diversion of minerals from eastern DRC,\\\" an expert in transnational crime tells our contributor, Th\\u00e9odore de Kerros, in his story today from the coltan mines of the Democratic Republic of Congo.\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1183, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\", \"score\": 0.9998828966740747, \"rank\": 0.00011695347558067581, \"text\": \"Congolese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\"}, {\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.112379164000526e-29, \"text\": \"DRC\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Conflict will need more than deadlines to be solved.\\\"\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Christian Science Monitor's coverage of the war between Hamas and Israel, and related articles.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1537, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Science_Monitor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Christian Science Monitor\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Science_Monitor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Science_Monitor\"}, {\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.267643330927485e-17, \"text\": \"Hamas\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\"}, {\"begin\": 1607, \"end\": 1613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999999996789484, \"rank\": 3.200729235682445e-10, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Already a subscriber?Log in  Already have a subscription?Activate it  Join the Monitor community.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Already a subscriber?Log in to hide ads.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. swimmer Katie Ledecky became the second swimmer in history to win gold in an event at four straight Summer Olympic Games, winning the 800 free.\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1792, \"end\": 1805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Ledecky now holds nine gold medals, winning her latest 12 years to the day after her first.\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading...  Aug. 05, 2024, 12:06 p.m. ET|Nanterre, France  Every year on Aug. 3, Katie Ledecky is reminded of her first Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2076, \"end\": 2082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.996964877191162, \"rank\": 0.0022439890210931655, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2106, \"end\": 2119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was just 15 years old, a reserved high schooler who had surprisingly made the U.S. swim team for the London Games.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then she went out and shocked the world, beating everyone in the 800-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Twelve years later to the day, Ms. Ledecky did it again.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not a stunner, but one for the ages.\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medal No.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2482, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"9.\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Ledecky capped another stellar Olympics by becoming only the second swimmer to win an event at four straight Summer Games, holding off Ariarne Titmus, the \\\"Terminator,\\\" to win the 800 free Aug. 3.\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Ms. Ledecky's second gold medal in Paris and the ninth of her remarkable career, which marked another milestone.\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2731, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0557915705313757e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She became only the sixth Olympian to reach that figure, joining swimmer Mark Spitz, track star Carl Lewis, Soviet gymnast Larisa Latynina, and Finnish runner Paavo Nurmi in a tie for second place.\", \"from\": 2810, \"to\": 3007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2836, \"end\": 2844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999962544983882, \"rank\": 3.7456419318276446e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2883, \"end\": 2893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Spitz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Spitz\"}, {\"begin\": 2906, \"end\": 2916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 2918, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8756301185324113e-16, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 2954, \"end\": 2961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"score\": 0.9999999888486856, \"rank\": 6.646020204055418e-09, \"text\": \"Finnish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Finland\"}, {\"begin\": 2969, \"end\": 2980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paavo Nurmi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paavo_Nurmi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With nine Olympic gold medals and 14 total, Ms. Ledecky\\u00a0is the most decorated American female Olympian.\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3086, \"end\": 3094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999569809, \"rank\": 4.277625929036907e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3102, \"end\": 3110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.999962544983882, \"rank\": 3.7456419318276446e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only athlete to win more golds: swimmer Michael Phelps with 23.\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.821515727726886e-112, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Ledecky was very aware of the significance of the date.\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Every Aug. 3, the video [of her first Olympic gold] gets posted somewhere and you kind of reminisce,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So, when I saw it was Aug. 3, I was like, 'Oh boy, I have got to get the job done.'\\\"\", \"from\": 3356, \"to\": 3441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That she did, going faster than her winning time in Tokyo to finish in 8 minutes, 11.04 seconds.\", \"from\": 3443, \"to\": 3539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3495, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999998893145, \"rank\": 1.1072391724434725e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Titmus was right on her shoulder nearly the entire race, but Ms. Ledecky pulled away in the final 100.\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3544, \"end\": 3550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Titmus, who beat Ms. Ledecky in the 400 freestyle, settled for silver at 8:12.29.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3652, \"end\": 3658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze went to another American, Paige Madden at 8:13.00.\", \"from\": 3734, \"to\": 3795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999569809, \"rank\": 4.277625929036907e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3771, \"end\": 3783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige Madden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Phelps had been the only swimmer to win the same event at four straight Olympics, taking gold in the 200 individual medley at Athens, Beijing, London, and Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3801, \"end\": 3807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7511983828307818e-14, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 3927, \"end\": 3933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1485988772004465e-18, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3935, \"end\": 3942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.970785876369686e-22, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.2824341687757177e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 3956, \"end\": 3970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.526604498038155e-32, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now he's got company.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Titmus added some perspective to Ms. Ledecky's consistency over the last dozen years, noting where she was when the American won that first gold in London.\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4000, \"end\": 4006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999569809, \"rank\": 4.277625929036907e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4148, \"end\": 4154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.2824341687757177e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was in grade six in primary school,\\\" Ms. Titmus said.\", \"from\": 4157, \"to\": 4213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4201, \"end\": 4207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's how remarkable she is.\\\"\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their friendly rivalry has driven both to greater heights.\", \"from\": 4247, \"to\": 4305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They each won two golds and four medals at these games, which pushed Ms. Ledecky to 14 overall and left the 23-year-old Aussie with four golds and eight medals in her career.\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4480, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To think that ...\", \"from\": 4482, \"to\": 4500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I challenged her into her fourth consecutive in the 800 is pretty cool,\\\" Ms. Titmus said.\", \"from\": 4501, \"to\": 4590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4578, \"end\": 4584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel very honored and privileged to be her rival, and I hope I have made her a better athlete.\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4688, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has certainly made me become the athlete I am.\", \"from\": 4689, \"to\": 4739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt so privileged to race alongside her.\\\"\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Ledecky has dominated the distance freestyle events over the last dozen years - and is not done yet.\", \"from\": 4786, \"to\": 4890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's made it clear she plans to keep swimming at least through the 2028 Los Angeles Games.\", \"from\": 4891, \"to\": 4982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not easy,\\\" Ms. Ledecky said.\", \"from\": 4984, \"to\": 5018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will take it year by year, and we will see if I can keep giving everything I have got for as long as I have left in me.\\\"\", \"from\": 5019, \"to\": 5142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Summer McIntosh stamped herself as one of the swimming stars of the Paris Olympics with her third individual gold medal, winning the 200 individual medley.\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5144, \"end\": 5159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 17-year-old Canadian chased down American Alex Walsh and held off another U.S. swimmer, Kate Douglass, to finish in an Olympic record of 2:06.56.\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5317, \"end\": 5325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9429860834145922, \"rank\": 0.060461037112183175, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 5338, \"end\": 5346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999569809, \"rank\": 4.277625929036907e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5347, \"end\": 5357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexandra_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 5393, \"end\": 5406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. Douglass grabbed the silver in the star-studded final at 2:06.92, but the Americans lost the bronze when Ms. Walsh, the silver medalist in this event at Tokyo who recorded a time of 2:07.06, was disqualified because she did not finish the backstroke segment on her back.\", \"from\": 5452, \"to\": 5726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5456, \"end\": 5464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9999999999527063, \"rank\": 4.766064784216858e-11, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 5609, \"end\": 5614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999998893145, \"rank\": 1.1072391724434725e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylee McKeown, who touched fourth, was bumped up to the bronze at 2:08.08.\", \"from\": 5728, \"to\": 5803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5728, \"end\": 5742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a bitter blow for Ms. Walsh, whose younger sister, Gretchen, has won a gold medal and two silvers in Paris.\", \"from\": 5805, \"to\": 5919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5863, \"end\": 5871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6313468820645404e-18, \"text\": \"Gretchen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 5913, \"end\": 5918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0557915705313757e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. McIntosh set several world records ahead of the Paris Olympics, and she backed up the enormous expectations by claiming a starring role at La Defense Arena along with L\\u00e9on Marchand and Ms. Ledecky.\", \"from\": 5921, \"to\": 6122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5925, \"end\": 5933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.698296630008252e-13, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 6092, \"end\": 6105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803534156, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ms. McIntosh also won gold medals in the 200 butterfly and 400 IM, plus a silver in the 400 freestyle.\", \"from\": 6124, \"to\": 6226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6128, \"end\": 6136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.698296630008252e-13, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She fell just 0.88 seconds - the margin of her loss to Ms. Titmus - shy of matching Mr. Marchand's four individual golds.\", \"from\": 6227, \"to\": 6348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6315, \"end\": 6323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999930140136989, \"rank\": 6.986034010534587e-06, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's pretty surreal,\\\" said Ms. McIntosh, who became the first Canadian athlete to win three golds in a single Olympics.\", \"from\": 6350, \"to\": 6470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6382, \"end\": 6390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.698296630008252e-13, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 6413, \"end\": 6421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9429860834145922, \"rank\": 0.060461037112183175, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just so proud of myself and how I have been able to recover and manage events.\\\"\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States made up for a disappointing showing in Tokyo by setting a world record in the 4x100 mixed medley relay.\", \"from\": 6558, \"to\": 6679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6562, \"end\": 6575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.999999993813617, \"rank\": 6.1864166581956885e-09, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6615, \"end\": 6620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999998893145, \"rank\": 1.1072391724434725e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Murphy, Nic Fink, Gretchen Walsh, and Torri Huske held off China for a winning time of 3:37.43, breaking the mark of 3:37.58 set by Britain when it won gold in the wild and woolly event's Olympic debut three years ago.\", \"from\": 6681, \"to\": 6904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6681, \"end\": 6692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.315521444346064e-17, \"text\": \"Ryan Murphy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\"}, {\"begin\": 6724, \"end\": 6735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}, {\"begin\": 6745, \"end\": 6750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999998681233, \"rank\": 1.3194359254558134e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 6818, \"end\": 6825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9996686015904043, \"rank\": 0.00033150826403894663, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With each team picking two men and two women, the U.S. and China both went with their male swimmers in the first two legs.\", \"from\": 6906, \"to\": 7028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6965, \"end\": 6970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999998681233, \"rank\": 1.3194359254558134e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Murphy put the U.S. in front on the backstroke, China's Qin Haiyang slipped past Mr. Fink on the breaststroke, but Ms. Walsh stormed back in front for the Americans on the butterfly before Ms. Huske held off Yang Junxuan to secure the gold.\", \"from\": 7030, \"to\": 7274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7082, \"end\": 7087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999998681233, \"rank\": 1.3194359254558134e-10, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 7090, \"end\": 7101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"score\": 0.9999938624993854, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qin Haiyang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\"}, {\"begin\": 7119, \"end\": 7123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0578431691286261e-43, \"text\": \"Fink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nic_Fink\"}, {\"begin\": 7242, \"end\": 7254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Junxuan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Junxuan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Junxuan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yang_Junxuan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Ms. Huske, it was her second gold to go with two silvers in Paris.\", \"from\": 7276, \"to\": 7346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7340, \"end\": 7345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0557915705313757e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Chinese team, which also included Xu Jiayu and Zhang Yufei, took silver in 3:37.55.\", \"from\": 7348, \"to\": 7435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7352, \"end\": 7359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999659030442, \"rank\": 3.400014674616553e-08, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 7386, \"end\": 7394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Jiayu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xu Jiayu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Jiayu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Jiayu\"}, {\"begin\": 7399, \"end\": 7410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9727864122998912, \"rank\": 0.027972027972023663, \"text\": \"Zhang Yufei\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze went to Australia in 3:38.76.\", \"from\": 7436, \"to\": 7476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7455, \"end\": 7464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999597384893, \"rank\": 3.592157661107811e-08, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Marchand swam the breaststroke leg for France but could not add to his already impressive haul.\", \"from\": 7478, \"to\": 7577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7482, \"end\": 7490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999930140136989, \"rank\": 6.986034010534587e-06, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 7521, \"end\": 7527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.996964877191162, \"rank\": 0.0022439890210931655, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French finished fourth, more than two seconds behind the Aussies.\", \"from\": 7578, \"to\": 7647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7582, \"end\": 7588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.40127062600593305, \"rank\": 0.8008252925394214, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the British won gold in 2021, the Americans finished fifth.\", \"from\": 7649, \"to\": 7713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7658, \"end\": 7665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9987216596065214, \"rank\": 0.001274500670478555, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain was seventh this time.\", \"from\": 7714, \"to\": 7744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7714, \"end\": 7721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9996686015904043, \"rank\": 0.00033150826403894663, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Krist\\u00f3f Mil\\u00e1k of Hungary won the men's 100 butterfly, chasing down three swimmers on the return lap.\", \"from\": 7746, \"to\": 7846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7746, \"end\": 7759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krist\\u00f3f_Mil\\u00e1k\", \"score\": 0.9999999973315425, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Krist\\u00f3f Mil\\u00e1k\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krist\\u00f3f_Mil\\u00e1k\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krist\\u00f3f_Mil\\u00e1k\"}, {\"begin\": 7763, \"end\": 7770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5014402826002918e-12, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Mil\\u00e1k was only fourth at the turn, but he rallied to touch in 49.90.\", \"from\": 7848, \"to\": 7920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada grabbed the silver and bronze, with Josh Liendo finishing in 49.99 and Ilya Kharun next at 50.45.\", \"from\": 7921, \"to\": 8025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7921, \"end\": 7927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9293991927065979, \"rank\": 0.0759494747850159, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 7964, \"end\": 7968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9998849983569797, \"rank\": 0.0001150085825149044, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr. Mil\\u00e1k had failed to defend his Olympic title in the 200 butterfly, settling for a silver behind French star Mr. Marchand.\", \"from\": 8027, \"to\": 8152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8127, \"end\": 8133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.40127062600593305, \"rank\": 0.8008252925394214, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 8143, \"end\": 8151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999930140136989, \"rank\": 6.986034010534587e-06, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}]}, {\"sente